n\"><ul class=\"blockList\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px;\"><li class=\"blockList\" style=\"list-style: none; margin-bottom: 15px; line-height: 1.4;\"><dl><dt style=\"font-size: 12px; font-weight: bold; margin: 10px 0px 0px; color: rgb(78, 78, 78);\">All Implemented Interfaces:</dt><dd style=\"margin: 5px 0px 10px; font-family: &quot;DejaVu Serif&quot;, Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif;\"><code style=\"font-family: &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; padding-top: 4px; margin-top: 8px; line-height: 1.4em;\"><a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/10/docs/api/java/io/Serializable.html\" title=\"interface in java.io\" style=\"text-decoration-line: none; color: rgb(74, 103, 130);\">Serializable</a></code>,&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; padding-top: 4px; margin-top: 8px; line-height: 1.4em;\"><a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/10/docs/api/java/lang/Cloneable.html\" title=\"interface in java.lang\" style=\"text-decoration-line: none; color: rgb(74, 103, 130);\">Cloneable</a></code></dd></dl><hr><pre style=\"font-family: &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace;\">public class <span class=\"typeNameLabel\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">SimpleDateFormat</span>\nextends <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/10/docs/api/java/text/DateFormat.html\" title=\"class in java.text\" style=\"text-decoration-line: none; color: rgb(74, 103, 130);\">DateFormat</a></pre><div class=\"block\" style=\"margin: 3px 10px 2px 0px; color: rgb(71, 71, 71); font-family: &quot;DejaVu Serif&quot;, Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif;\"><code style=\"font-family: &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; padding-top: 4px; margin-top: 8px; line-height: 1.4em;\">SimpleDateFormat</code>&nbsp;is a concrete class for formatting and parsing dates in a locale-sensitive manner. It allows for formatting (date → text), parsing (text → date), and normalization.<p><code style=\"font-family: &q